To compute \(37562_9 + 41724_9\), start by converting each base-9 number to base-10.

First, convert \(37562_9\):
\[
37562_9 = 3 \cdot 9^4 + 7 \cdot 9^3 + 5 \cdot 9^2 + 6 \cdot 9^1 + 2 \cdot 9^0
\]
\[
= 3 \cdot 6561 + 7 \cdot 729 + 5 \cdot 81 + 6 \cdot 9 + 2 \cdot 1
\]
\[
= 19683 + 5103 + 405 + 54 + 2
\]
\[
= 25247_{10}
\]

Next, convert \(41724_9\):
\[
41724_9 = 4 \cdot 9^4 + 1 \cdot 9^3 + 7 \cdot 9^2 + 2 \cdot 9^1 + 4 \cdot 9^0
\]
\[
= 4 \cdot 6561 + 1 \cdot 729 + 7 \cdot 81 + 2 \cdot 9 + 4 \cdot 1
\]
\[
= 26244 + 729 + 567 + 18 + 4
\]
\[
= 27562_{10}
\]

Now, add the base-10 equivalents:
\[
25247_{10} + 27562_{10} = 52809_{10}
\]

Finally, convert \(52809_{10}\) back to base-9:
Find the largest power of 9 that fits into 52809.

\[
52809 \div 6561 \approx 8 \quad (\text{so the coefficient for } 9^4 \text{ is } 8)
\]
\[
52809 - 8 \cdot 6561 = 52809 - 52488 = 321
\]

Continue to the next power:
\[
321 \div 729 \approx 0 \quad (\text{so the coefficient for } 9^3 \text{ is } 0)
\]

Then:
\[
321 \div 81 \approx 3 \quad (\text{so the coefficient for } 9^2 \text{ is } 3)
\]
\[
321 - 3 \cdot 81 = 321 - 243 = 78
\]

Continuing to the next power:
\[
78 \div 9 = 8 \quad (\text{so the coefficient for } 9^1 \text{ is } 8)
\]
\[
78 - 8 \cdot 9 = 78 - 72 = 6
\]

Finally:
\[
6 \div 1 = 6 \quad (\text{so the coefficient for } 9^0 \text{ is } 6)
\]

Thus:
\[
52809_{10} = 80386_{9}
\]

Summarized:
\[
37562_9 + 41724_9 = 37562_{9} \rightarrow 25247_{10} + 41724_{9} \rightarrow 27562_{10} = 52809_{10} \rightarrow 80386_{9}
\]
